					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>The commentary of Japheth ben Ali ha-Levi on the Song of Songs and Ruth (fragments).</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jrb">Hebrew, Judeo-Arabic</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="161v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perushim</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרושים</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="en">Japheth ben Ali, ha-Levi,‏ active 10th century</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="he">יפת בן עלי, הלוי </persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>The volume contains Yefet's Arabic commentary on Ruth and the Song of Soings. The pointed and accentuated Hebrew text with an Arabic translation is embodied.</p>
							</note>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">תם  תפסיר שיר השירים ב[...] אללה ועונה ממא עלקה העבד הנצרך לרחמי צורו <name type="person" role="scribe">שמואל בן יוסף</name> כוגך נ"ע וכאן אלפראג מנה <date when="1331" calendar="Hijri-qamari">יום אלכמיס ראבע ועשרין אייר אלמואפק לשעבאן סנה אתנין ותלתין ושבע מאות לישמעאל</date> תפסיר אלמעלם אבו עלי.<locus from="161r" to="161v"/>
							</colophon>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="1v" to="45r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Ruth</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="45v" to="161v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Song of Songs</title>
							</msItem>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex. </support>
								<extent>161 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>170</height>
										<width>130</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>122</height>
										<width>95</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>161 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>17 quires of 10 leaves each (except the 13th and 17th which have 8 and 3 leaves respectively). </p>
									<p>The quires are signed with Arabic words on theupper margin of the first page.  </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>Lacunae after folios: 12, 21, 31, 45, 48, 61, 115.<p>Partially water-damaged. </p>
									<p>Several pages with damaged margins. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="17" writtenLines="17">
									<p>Separate title-page, supplied by a much later hand. </p>
									<p>The colophon is supplied twice, the second one being added in a more recent hand. </p>
									<p>The pointed and accentuated Hebrew text with an Arabic translation is embodied. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="3">
							<summary>Square and semi-cursive script of the 14th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Shemu᾿el ben Yosef</name>: inscribed, folio 161v.</summary>
